commit.message: Changing serialVersionUID from Expression as its hashCode was changed (see commit 9934f34)
With adding a new member variable (prefix) the class' serialization is different and the serialVersionUID has to be changed
Adding documentation to JarRunner triggering the JAR integration tests
Updating to new Maven Central Repo page
Further adoption to use the prefix string consistently in the code
Now using an empty prefix for default namespace (as Michael commented in his PR review) and added some consistency in prefix handling
Adding multi prefix for namespace XML test documents and tests for RNG & XSD
Adding regression tests validating with UN/CEFACT Cross Industry Invoice (CII) grammar an EN16931 (EU norm) example
Adding three regression tests validating with UBL 2.3 grammar (order, invoice and credit-note)
Linux requires adjustment to test references and tests..
Adding three regression tests for UBL 2.1 credit note and invoice being used in EN16931 EU e-invoice norm
Fixing XSD from old external W3C xmldsig reference with erroneous DTD in front (no longer existent in older version) as MSV uses this DTD to validate the file - which seems a correct assumption
Adding OASIS UBL 2.1 grammar for invoice & credit-note (part of EN16931) & some test documents from EN16931 validator https://github.com/ConnectingEurope/eInvoicing-EN16931/tree/master/ubl/examples
Adding back Maven fail-safe plugin (integration test calling the msv.jar file via commandline) with version back to root pom.xml to use a specific full release version and not some milestone
Adding command line integration test for validation of ODF 1.3 - added documents for ODF 1.3 (grammar and file - one manually edited wrong.xml for testing a wrong XML)
Enabling/refactoring JAR integration test for command line functionality

Next iteration step, adding Prefix to SimpleNameClass, but not yet working for <rng:name> as in http://docs.oasis-open.org/office/OpenDocument/v1.3/os/schemas/OpenDocument-v1.3-schema-rng.html#8705 - shall we add prefix to NameClass interface?
